\par\par \uc2 Business/Financial Desk; SECTB\par \b \uc2 Binance\uc2  Is Hit by a $570 Million Hack\b0\par\par\uc2 By Ephrat Livni \par \uc2 452 \uc2 words\par \uc2 8 October 2022\par \uc2 The New York Times\par \uc2 NYTF\par \uc2 Late Edition - Final\par 4\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2022 The New York Times Company.  All Rights Reserved. \par \par \uc2 The world's biggest cryptocurrency exchange confirmed that assets were stolen from the Binance Smart Chain network, the latest in a series of attacks on so-called cross-chain bridges.\par \par \uc2 Binance\uc2 , the world's biggest cryptocurrency exchange, confirmed on Friday that $570 million had been stolen in a hack of a \uc2 blockchain\uc2  it runs that serves as a bridge for asset transfers between networks. The attack on the Binance Smart Chain network highlighted weaknesses in decentralized finance, or DeFi, where transactions are controlled by code.\par \par \uc2 ''Software code is never bug free,'' \uc2 Binance\uc2 's chief executive, \uc2 Changpeng Zhao\uc2 , said in an interview with CNBC. He emphasized that no users had lost money in the hack but said that so-called cross-chain bridges were particularly vulnerable to hacks and the industry needed to get better at learning from them.\par \par \uc2 ''We have seen a series of attacks on targeting vulnerabilities in cross-chain bridges,'' Binance Smart Chain wrote in a blog post apologizing to users. ''We will openly share the details of the postmortem and all lessons on how to implement more advanced security measures to shore-up these vulnerabilities.''\par \par \uc2 In August, the \uc2 blockchain\uc2  research company \uc2 Chainalysis\uc2  estimated that $2 billion worth of cryptocurrency had been stolen in 13 cross-chain bridge attacks, mostly in 2022. In March, an attack drained $600 million from a bridge behind the crypto-powered video game Axie Infinity. In February, $325 million was stolen from the Wormhole network.\par \par \uc2 These exploits show that a reliance on code for control of DeFi platforms leaves these systems exposed, and that in emergency situations, decentralization can be an obstacle to quickly resolving issues. The \uc2 Binance\uc2  chain ecosystem is run by a community of users, known as validators, who hold tokens and can vote on proposed code changes.\par \par \uc2 ''Decentralized chains are not designed to be stopped, but by contacting community validators one by one, we were able to stop the incident from spreading,'' Binance Smart Chain said in its statement. ''This delayed closure, but we were able to minimize the loss.''\par \par \uc2 Now, the Binance Smart Chain community will hold a vote on next steps, including whether to freeze the stolen funds and allot a bounty for catching the hackers, offering up to 10 percent of the value of the stolen assets.\par \par \uc2 Vitalik Buterin\uc2 , one of the founders of the Ethereum network -- and the second-most-popular cryptocurrency, Ether -- has been a vocal critic of cross-chain bridges, noting that they have ''fundamental security limits.''\par \par \uc2 ''Software code is never bug free,'' Changpeng Zhao, Binance's chief executive, said on Friday. (PHOTOGRAPH BY Benoit Tessier/Reuters FOR THE NEW YORK TIMES) \par \par \uc2 Document NYTF000020221008eia80003j\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw284\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4260\pichgoal600
